      "content": "i get that, but my doctor is super busy and it's a hassle to make another appointment just for this. it feels like overkill to keep taking pills when there isn't even any redness or pain left. isn't the whole point of the medicine to kill the bacteria? if the bacteria are dead, why does the timing matter so much? it seems like a waste of medication at this point.",
